E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishna%20says%20cardboard%20protects%20plants%20from%20heat%20waves%20while%20keeping%20the%20soil%20moist%20and%20preventing%20pest%20attacks.%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F186864%2Fmumbai-girl-recycles-waste-organic-compost-raises-lakhs-dharavi-kids%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUsing%20cardboard%20%3C%2Fa%3Ereduces%20evaporation%20from%20the%20top%20exposed%20soil%2C%20preventing%20it%20from%20drying%20out%20by%20holding%20the%20moisture%20in.%20It%20promotes%20more%20steady%20soil%20temperature%20overall.%20It%20will%20suppress%20weed%20growth%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20As%20a%20mulch%20to%20nourish%20soil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishna%20says%20using%20cardboard%20as%20mulch%20nourishes%20the%20soil%20while%20it%E2%80%99s%20decomposing.%20She%20also%20advises%20using%20cardboards%20that%20are%20100%20percent%20recyclable%20or%20compostable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20As%20a%20filling%20for%20large%20grow%20bags%20for%20composting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishna%20says%20filling%20grow%20bags%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F278855%2Furban-garden-homemaker-grow-vegetable-fruits-flowers-organic-composting%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecardboard%20for%20composting%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehelps%20them%20transform%20into%20rich%20fertilisers%20with%20the%20help%20of%20worms.%20When%20tossed%20in%20the%20soil%2C%20worms%20munch%20through%20the%20cardboard%20until%20it%20breaks%20as%20it%20is%20biodegradable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20advises%20using%20cardboard%20boxes%20as%20seedling%20boxes%20and%20hard%20ones%20for%20planters%20as%20well.%20%E2%80%9CNext%20time%20you%20get%20them%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20throw%20them%20away%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20advises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned